ain—including narratives, conversations, models, and metaphors—and detailed analysis of how young pain sufferers make meaning through interactions with others, her book reveals that however private pain may be, making sense of it is profoundly social.  aMode of access: Internet via World Wide Web.  aIn English.0 aDescription based on online resource; title from PDF title page (publisher's Web site, viewed 29. Mai 2023) 0aPain clinicszUnited States. 0aPain in childrenxSocial aspects. 0aPain in children. 0aPainxSocial aspects. 7aSOCIAL SCIENCE / Anthropology / Cultural & Social.2bisacsh  aadolescent patients.  abiomedicine.  achildren with unexplained pain.  achronic pain in kids.  achronic pain.  afeeling pain.  aillness in children and teens.  amysterious ailments.  amysterious illness.  aneurobiology of pain.  aneurobiology.  apain clinics.  apain in children.  apain management.  apain symptoms children and teens.  apain symptoms kids.  apediatric pain management.  apediatric pain.  ateenager chronic pain.  aunexplained pain.  awest clinic california.08iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertUniversity of California Press Complete Package 2014-2015z97831106211120 cprintz978052028521740uhttps://doi.org/10.1525/978052096076340uhttps://www.degruyter.com/isbn/9780520960763423Coveruhttps://www.degruyter.com/document/cover/isbn/9780520960763/original  a978-3-11-062111-2  University of California Press Complete Package 2014-2015c2014d2015  aEBA_FAO  aEBA_UCA_YUP  aGBV-deGruyter-alles  aZDB-23-UCY